headline: Wells Fargo hit with downgrade, U.S. Bancorp rating bumped on profit rebound hopes
summary: Investing.com -- Raymond James downgraded Wells Fargo to Market perform, saying the stock’s recent rally has priced in much of the upside from improving profitability, while upgrading U.S. Bancorp (BVMF:USBC34) to Strong buy on expectations for a turnaround in operating leverage and sentiment.
